parameters.description:
Types of logs:
 * `console` - This is the default if the value is not provided. All logs lines displayed in the job's runtime environment.
 * `stdout` - Log lines displayed in the stderr of the job's runtime environment.
 * `stderr` - Log lines displayed in the stderr of the job's runtime environment.
 * `stdoutstderr` - Interleaved stdout and stderr.
 * `prepareoutput` - Log lines generated by the environment preparing the job.
parameters.name: logType

parameters.description: Max number of log lines to fetch. Will be overridden by the configuration's limit if this value exceeds the configuration's limit, or if this value is not provided.
parameters.name: limit

parameters.description: The index of the current body of logs to start fetching from. 0 by default and typically won't be used for a timestamp-based offset log fetching strategy.
parameters.name: offset

parameters.description: The epoch time in nanoseconds to start fetching from, such as "1543538813745986325". "0" by default and will typically be used for a timestamp-based offset log fetching strategy.
parameters.name: latestTimeNano

200.description:

If the problem detector detects no problem, then the client should expect * a `LogsWithProblemSuggestion` object with only logs If the problem detector detects the problem, then the client should expect * a `LogsWithProblemSuggestion` object with logs with problem suggestions
